snippet.textDisplay: Ok so I never ever ever comment on videos. Liane, I just broke up with the love of my life in Jan. It’s been about 3 months now. We were together for 11 years. ELEVEN. I am 28. We did it all together, grew up together, grew together, fought together, loved hard. Love is strong and unconditional love is real. He cheated and snapped me in half. I would wish that heartbreak in NO ONE. And idk what Don did but this is my story. It broke more than just me, it was devastating to my family of course and his as well. Everyone is hurting now. And like you, I forgive. It’s the Holy Spirit in me for sure. Becoming bitter, not forgiving will never cause me to heal. Will never be able to move forward. For me, not for him, forgiveness is important.  But it’s important to always love you first. And for him too. It sounds like Don has things he needs to find in himself, and like your friend said, this is a time when people go to sex, media, empty things to fill a void . But the only thing that can fill someone up is God. We will continue looking to temporary validation, empty things that will never ever fill us. Turn to God. This happens for a reason, whether it’s for something bigger in our lives, or even that person in the future. But always know you cannot change a person. No matter all the kindness you give to someone, you cannot save anyone. People can change only if and when theyyyyy choose to . If they want to change, they will. They’ll ex out the things that bury them and the habits they need to break up with . Your character is your greatest value. You can only build that through yourself and God. For you, remember you’re not called to save your partner. You’re called to walk with your partner. If he’s not on his two feet and whole in himself he cannot. Let the Lord work and let his plan shine through. It comes in waves. Some days I am okay. Some days I’m feeling strong and some days I am sobbing so incredibly hard that it hurts my chest. When you’ve built a life with someone it is not going to be easy. You chose that person. And it’s unfair. But uncomfortability creates growth. When you’re feeling the most uncomfortable, remember you are right where you need to be. You’re going to want to keep doing things you knew and you’ll be confused but remember PUT IT ALL IN GODS HANDS. He’s working it out. I promise . My love is with you. You are so valuable Liane.
